{"article_id":"mC06XQgbjuYar5iT","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Hiring remained moderate at the end of the year","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"as employers appeared undaunted by the fiscal cliff gridlock in December .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"Overall , the labor market 's performance in 2012 was pretty lackluster","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"and hiring was not strong enough","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"to get the nation out of its economic rut ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"economists said .","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"The economy added 155,000 jobs in December ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"bringing the total number of jobs","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"created in 2012","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"to 1.84 million ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"the Labor Department said Friday .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"The unemployment rate held steady at 7.8 % .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Economists","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"surveyed by Briefing.com","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"expected the report to show","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that 150,000 jobs were created last month","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"and the unemployment rate remained unchanged .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Friday 's report reflected revisions","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"the Labor Department made for 2012 ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"which included raising the November unemployment rate to 7.8 % , up from the original 7.7 % .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"The private sector continued to drive the growth ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"adding 168,000 jobs ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"while government employers shed 13,000 positions .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"Employment increased in health care , food services and drinking places and manufacturing .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Construction jobs were also up ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"likely as a result of rebuilding efforts after Hurricane Sandy .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"Friday 's report appeared a day after a separate survey by payroll processor ADP showed","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"private employers boosted their hiring last month ,","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"adding 215,000 jobs .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"But December 's overall figures were only slightly better than 2012 's average growth of 153,000 per month ,","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"which mirrored the 2011 pace .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"That 's not enough","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"to make a significant dent in the unemployment rate ,","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"economists said .","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"`` The labor market survived the fiscal cliff ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"but continues to move sideways , ''","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"said Ellen Zentner , senior U.S. economist with Nomura Securities .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"Still , it seems clear the labor market is less resilient","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"than it has been for much of the post-World War II period ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"said Patrick O'Keefe , director of economic research at CohnReznick .","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"`` The job market does n't appear to have the bounce","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"it once did , ''","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"he said .","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"There remains a deep hole","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"left by the financial crisis","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"and millions are still out of work .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"The number of long-term unemployed stayed essentially unchanged at 4.8 million , or 39.1 % of the jobless .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"One positive note is that there was a notable rise in the number of unemployed","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"re-entering the market ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"O'Keefe said .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"The figure jumped nearly 8 % in December ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"possibly signaling a renewed sense of optimism among the jobless .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Wage growth also remained unimpressive ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"with average hourly earnings rising 2.1 % in 2012 .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"But that was not sufficient","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"to keep pace with rising prices .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"`` It 's better than backsliding ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"but it 's not enough","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"for workers to get ahead of inflation , ''","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"O'Keefe said .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":119,"left":65,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":65,"left":61,"right":64,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":61,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":64,"left":63,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":63,"left":2,"right":62,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":62,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":92,"right":117,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":84,"right":91,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":84,"left":78,"right":83,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":78,"left":75,"right":77,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":70,"right":74,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":70,"left":69,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":69,"left":68,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":68,"left":6,"right":67,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":67,"left":66,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":66,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":74,"left":72,"right":73,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":72,"left":71,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":71,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":73,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":77,"left":76,"right":19,"relation":"elaborat